{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"/sc:analyze --seq\n\nREAD-ONLY analysis only. Do not modify any files.\n\nCompare this assigned file against three refactoring release specs to identify whether each item is REDUNDANT, CONTRADICTED, OVERLAPPING, or UNAFFECTED.\n\nShared context:\nThe v3.5RigorFlowMerger improve-*.md files were written BEFORE these three refactoring releases were designed. The refactoring releases may render improve-file items:\n- REDUNDANT: the refactor already implements what the improve item proposes\n- CONTRADICTED: the refactor makes the improve item's target file/system incompatible or replaced\n- OVERLAPPING: partial overlap — the refactor implements some of the item but not all\n- UNAFFECTED: no relationship; item stands independently\n\nReference specs:\n1. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md\n2. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md\n3. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md\n\nAssigned file:\n/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-sprint-executor.md\n\nFor each item in the assigned file (SE-001, SE-002, SE-003, SE-004, SE-005), produce:\n\n**ITEM [ID]** — [title]\n- Status: REDUNDANT | CONTRADICTED | OVERLAPPING | UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence: cite specific section/file from which refactor spec(s) create the relationship\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS | REVISE (describe what changes) | REMOVE (reason)\n\nPay special attention — this file has the HIGHEST overlap risk:\n- SE-001 modifies sprint/executor.py gate completion logic — v3.0 also hooks into sprint/executor.py post-task (Section 4.5). v3.1 adds sprint CLI integration at the completion/release guard level (Section 10.2, item 2, tui.py; item 7 sprint CLI integration). Check whether SE-001's fail-closed logic is superseded by v3.1's transition validator.\n- SE-002 adds task_uid tracking to sprint/executor.py — v3.1 adds explicit audit_* states to sprint/models.py. Check whether the UID-based resume logic conflicts with the new state machine (e.g., can a task be in audit_task_running and have a UID-based resume invoked simultaneously?).\n- SE-004 auto-triggers diagnostic on N consecutive failures — v3.1's state machine has retry semantics with bounded attempt budgets (Section 4.4). Check whether SE-004's auto-diagnostic threshold is redundant with or conflicts with v3.1's retry exhaustion behavior.\n- SE-005 adds GateFailureSeverity enum (SEV1/SEV2/SEV3) to pipeline/models.py — v3.1 defines its own failure_class taxonomy (policy|transient|system|timeout|unknown) and severity model (Section 5.1, Section 3.1). These are different classification systems applied to the same gate failure events. This is the highest-risk contradiction in the entire improve-set.\n\nEnd with one paragraph summarizing the assigned file's overall disposition after the three refactors."},"uuid":"3f171d56-dea0-4cdc-9035-4a1b41b23e6a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:11.767Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
