{"parentUuid":"e98c8666-8da0-4508-927e-eb5e738dc615","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c899109a-85f0-4ce2-8d4b-537fc48bb9f2","agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_cmymJB1ExXaAApDy8CGjm9wp","type":"tool_result","content":"2:release: wiring-verification-gate-v1.0\n13:# Wiring Verification Gate v1.0 -- Release Specification\n15:## 1. Problem Statement\n19:pipeline's gate infrastructure validates documents -- not code integration. Components\n20:defined in specifications and decomposed into tasks can pass all existing gates while\n28:| DEVIATION_ANALYSIS_GATE | Defined at `roadmap/gates.py:712` but never wired into `_build_steps()` |\n29:| SprintGatePolicy | Exists at `sprint/executor.py:46-89` but `build_remediation_step` is not invoked from the sprint loop |\n30:| Trailing gate framework | `TrailingGateRunner` exists but `execute_sprint()` never calls it |\n32:**This release creates the first code-level gate in the pipeline.**\n36:## 2. Goals and Non-Goals\n38:### Goals\n46:### Non-Goals (v1.0)\n50:- Runtime behavioral verification (see Smoke Test Gate proposal)\n56:## 3. Architecture\n58:### 3.1 System Context\n64:pipeline/models.py                        audit/wiring_gate.py\n68:pipeline/gates.py\n69:  gate_passed() ────────────────────────>   evaluates WIRING_GATE\n71:sprint/executor.py\n72:  SprintGatePolicy ─────────────────────>   invokes wiring checks post-task\n74:pipeline/trailing_gate.py\n76:  resolve_gate_mode() ──────────────────>   scope-aware enforcement\n79:### 3.2 Module Architecture\n82:src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_gate.py    (NEW -- core analysis)\n89:    |--- run_wiring_analysis(target_dir) -> WiringReport\n91:    |--- check_wiring_report(content: str) -> bool    # SemanticCheck-compatible\n93:    |--- WIRING_GATE = GateCriteria(...)              # gate definition\n95:src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_config.py  (NEW -- configuration)\n100:    |--- load_wiring_config(path) -> WiringConfig\n103:### 3.3 Data Flow\n120:                | run_wiring_analysis()   |\n133:                | -> wiring-report.md     |\n140:                | gate_passed(            |\n141:                |   wiring-report.md,     |\n155:## 4. Detailed Design\n157:### 4.1 Data Models\n160:# src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_gate.py\n175:    \"\"\"A single wiring verification finding.\"\"\"\n197:    \"\"\"Aggregate wiring analysis results.\"\"\"\n226:### 4.2 Analysis Functions\n228:#### 4.2.1 Unwired Callable Analysis\n289:# This triggers detection:\n294:# This call site does NOT provide step_runner:\n296:# -> Finding: unwired_callable, PortifyExecutor.step_runner\n299:**Whitelist mechanism**: A `wiring_whitelist.yaml` file can list intentionally-optional\n305:# wiring_whitelist.yaml\n315:- `load_wiring_config()` MUST validate each entry against the schema above.\n318:    `WARNING: wiring_whitelist.yaml entry [N] malformed (missing: <field>), skipping.`\n319:- `load_wiring_config()` MUST NOT raise `WiringConfigError` for malformed entries\n320:  during Phase 1 shadow mode — the gate must continue running to preserve\n323:**Phase 2 note**: `load_wiring_config()` will be updated to raise `WiringConfigError`\n327:#### 4.2.2 Orphan Module Analysis\n350:# src/superclaude/cli/cli_portify/steps/validate_config.py\n354:# executor.py never contains:\n355:# from .steps.validate_config import run_validate_config\n356:# -> Finding: orphan_module, steps/validate_config.py::run_validate_config\n361:#### 4.2.3 Unwired Registry Analysis\n389:### 4.3 Report Format\n391:The wiring analysis emits a Markdown file with YAML frontmatter, conforming to\n392:the `GateCriteria` validation pattern used by all existing gates.\n396:gate: wiring-verification\n407:# Wiring Verification Report\n409:## Unwired Callables (1)\n411:### WF-001: PortifyExecutor.step_runner\n420:## Orphan Modules (2)\n422:### WF-002: steps/validate_config.py::run_validate_config\n430:### WF-003: steps/discover_components.py::run_discover_components\n438:## Summary\n450:Boolean and integer fields that are gate-evaluated (`analysis_complete`,\n458:errors; defensively handled, these produce gate failures rather than bypasses,\n484:the gate report alone, without diffing `wiring_whitelist.yaml` across commits.\n486:### 4.4 Gate Definition\n491:        \"gate\",\n535:used by `_high_severity_count_zero`, `_total_analyzed_consistent`, etc. in `roadmap/gates.py`.\n537:### 4.5 Sprint Integration\n539:The wiring gate hooks into the sprint runner at the post-task classification point.\n541:**Hook point**: `sprint/executor.py`, after `_classify_from_result_file()` returns,\n547:# In execute_phase_tasks() or _run_task_subprocess(), after classification:\n549:wiring_report_path = work_dir / f\"{task_id}-wiring-report.md\"\n550:report = run_wiring_analysis(target_dir=config.source_dir)\n551:emit_report(report, wiring_report_path)\n553:if config.wiring_gate_mode == \"shadow\":\n555:    logger.info(f\"[shadow] Wiring gate: {report.total_findings} findings\")\n556:elif config.wiring_gate_mode == \"soft\":\n559:        tui.warn(f\"Wiring gate: {report.total_findings} findings\")\n560:elif config.wiring_gate_mode == \"full\":\n562:    passed, reason = gate_passed(wiring_report_path, WIRING_GATE)\n571:wiring_gate_mode: Literal[\"off\", \"shadow\", \"soft\", \"full\"] = \"shadow\"\n574:### 4.6 Companion: Deviation Count Reconciliation\n577:the ranking), as a zero-cost companion that strengthens existing Link 1 gates.\n580:added to `SPEC_FIDELITY_GATE.semantic_checks` in `roadmap/gates.py`.\n592:## 5. File Manifest\n596:| `src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_gate.py` | CREATE | 250-300 | Core analysis engine, report emitter, gate definition |\n597:| `src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_config.py` | CREATE | 40-60 | Configuration dataclass, patterns, whitelist loader |\n598:| `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/config.py` | MODIFY | +5 | Add `wiring_gate_mode` field |\n599:| `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/executor.py` | MODIFY | +25 | Post-task wiring analysis hook |\n600:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` | MODIFY | +40 | `_deviation_counts_reconciled` semantic check |\n601:| `tests/audit/test_wiring_gate.py` | CREATE | 200-250 | Unit tests for all analysis functions |\n603:| `tests/audit/fixtures/` | CREATE | 50-80 | Python fixtures for wiring analysis tests |\n610:## 6. Interface Contracts\n612:### 6.1 Public API\n615:# Entry point for wiring analysis\n616:def run_wiring_analysis(\n620:    \"\"\"Analyze a directory for wiring verification issues.\n630:# Report emitter (Markdown + YAML frontmatter)\n636:    \"\"\"Write wiring report as Markdown with YAML frontmatter.\n642:# SemanticCheck-compatible function\n643:def check_wiring_report(content: str) -> bool:\n644:    \"\"\"Validate a wiring report passes all criteria.\n650:### 6.2 Configuration Contract\n655:    \"\"\"Configuration for wiring verification analysis.\"\"\"\n672:    # Path to wiring_whitelist.yaml. Entries suppress gate findings for matched symbols.\n674:    # Count of applied entries is reported in gate output frontmatter (Section 4.3.2).\n683:### 6.3 Gate Contract\n686:existing `gate_passed()` function in `pipeline/gates.py` without modification.\n692:| `gate` | string | Must be `\"wiring-verification\"` |\n695:| `unwired_count` | int | Must be 0 for gate pass |\n696:| `orphan_count` | int | Must be 0 for gate pass |\n697:| `registry_count` | int | Must be 0 for gate pass |\n704:## 7. Risk Assessment\n708:| R1: False positives from intentional `Optional[Callable]` hooks | High | Medium | Whitelist mechanism (`wiring_whitelist.yaml`) |\n709:| R2: AST parsing fails on complex Python patterns | Medium | Low | Graceful degradation: log warning, skip file, do not fail gate |\n717:## 8. Rollout Plan\n719:### Phase 1: Shadow (this release)\n737:- Results logged to `.sprint-state/wiring/` directory\n741:### Phase 2: Soft (release +1, pending shadow data review)\n745:- Block only at release scope (per `resolve_gate_mode()` which returns BLOCKING for release)\n746:- Override available via `--skip-wiring-gate` flag\n763:### Phase 3: Full (release +2, pending soft data review)\n769:### Rollout Decision Criteria\n780:## 9. Testing Strategy\n782:### 9.1 Coverage Requirements\n784:The test suite shall validate the wiring analysis gate across two layers.\n786:#### Unit Tests (minimum 14 tests, across 4 analyzer functions)\n794:- Parse error: source file with a Python syntax error — gate does not crash;\n815:**emit_report / gate** (minimum 3 tests):\n816:- Findings present → `gate_passed()` returns `(False, reason)`; report\n818:- No findings → `gate_passed()` returns `(True, None)`; report frontmatter\n822:  indicator character must parse without `yaml.YAMLError`; `gate_passed()`\n825:### 9.2 Integration Tests (minimum 2 tests)\n836:Behavioral contract (non-negotiable): `run_wiring_analysis()` on the fixture\n847:When the wiring gate executes in shadow mode within a sprint run, the following\n848:must hold after gate execution regardless of gate outcome:\n851:- No exception is propagated to the sprint runner\n854:### 9.3 Test Infrastructure\n858:**Coverage target**: ≥ 90% line coverage on `src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_gate.py`\n866:## 10. Success Criteria\n870:| SC-001 | Wiring gate detects `Optional[Callable] = None` never provided at call site | Unit test: `test_detect_unwired_callable_basic` |\n871:| SC-002 | Wiring gate detects orphan modules in `steps/` directories | Unit test: `test_detect_orphan_module` |\n872:| SC-003 | Wiring gate detects unresolvable registry entries | Unit test: `test_detect_unwired_registry` |\n873:| SC-004 | Report conforms to `GateCriteria` validation pattern | Unit test: `test_gate_passes_clean_report` |\n874:| SC-005 | `gate_passed()` evaluates `WIRING_GATE` without modification | Integration test: `test_cli_portify_fixture` |\n884:## 11. Dependency Map\n893:                  pipeline/gates.py\n894:                    gate_passed()\n896:                  pipeline/trailing_gate.py\n897:                    resolve_gate_mode()\n902:                  audit/wiring_gate.py -------> pipeline/models.py (import)\n905:                  audit/wiring_config.py        pipeline/gates.py (consumed by)\n908:                  sprint/executor.py (MODIFY) -> audit/wiring_gate.py (import)\n910:                  roadmap/gates.py (MODIFY) -- deviation count recon only\n913:**Zero changes to existing gate infrastructure.** The wiring gate is a new consumer\n914:of the existing `GateCriteria`/`SemanticCheck`/`gate_passed()` pattern.\n918:## 12. Tasklist Index (for sprint execution)\n922:| T01 | Data models (`WiringFinding`, `WiringReport`, `WiringConfig`) | `wiring_gate.py` (partial), `wiring_config.py` | -- |\n923:| T02 | Unwired callable analysis (`analyze_unwired_callables`) | `wiring_gate.py` (partial) | T01 |\n924:| T03 | Orphan module analysis (`analyze_orphan_modules`) | `wiring_gate.py` (partial) | T01 |\n925:| T04 | Unwired registry analysis (`analyze_unwired_registries`) | `wiring_gate.py` (partial) | T01 |\n926:| T05 | Report emitter and `WIRING_GATE` constant | `wiring_gate.py` (complete) | T01 |\n927:| T06 | Unit tests for T02-T04 + test fixtures | `tests/audit/test_wiring_gate.py` (minimum 14 unit tests per Section 9.1), `tests/audit/fixtures/` (SC-010 fixture structure per Section 9.2 behavioral contract) | T02, T03, T04 |\n928:| T07 | Sprint integration (shadow mode hook) | `sprint/executor.py` (modify), `sprint/config.py` (modify) | T05 |\n929:| T08 | Deviation count reconciliation | `roadmap/gates.py` (modify) | -- |\n931:| T10 | Integration test: cli-portify fixture | `tests/audit/test_wiring_integration.py` | T06, T07 |\n940:## Appendix A: Forensic Report Cross-Reference\n947:| Link 3 does not exist | Section 5 | T05+T07: gate definition + sprint integration |\n952:## Appendix B: Naming Convention Reference"}]},"uuid":"cebb5a49-8b99-49de-b880-9833a4b168df","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:37.481Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e98c8666-8da0-4508-927e-eb5e738dc615","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
