{"parentUuid":"603b3ab8-5b44-44c0-983e-6479ef011924","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c899109a-85f0-4ce2-8d4b-537fc48bb9f2","agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_z9WcaWmN7xRlMucNrSKFL2G5","type":"tool_result","content":"1:# Anti-Instincts Gate -- Unified Specification\n16:## 1. Problem Statement\n20:LLMs exhibit several correlated tendencies when generating multi-phase roadmaps from specifications. These tendencies cause systematic omission of integration wiring, undischarged scaffolding obligations, and dropped code-level requirements -- even when the output passes all existing format and fidelity gates.\n29:| Extraction-stage requirement loss (upstream guard) | `spec_structural_audit.py` | V1-C |\n40:## 2. Evidence: The cli-portify Bug\n44:### What the spec defined\n53:### What the roadmap produced\n59:### How existing gates failed\n61:The `SPEC_FIDELITY_GATE` enforces `high_severity_count == 0` deterministically, but the LLM generating the severity counts shared the same blindspot as the generator. The deterministic enforcement was sound; the LLM input to that gate was wrong.\n63:### How each module in this spec would have caught it\n70:| `spec_structural_audit.py` | Pseudocode block + `PROGRAMMATIC_RUNNERS` registry + `def _run_*` signatures inflate structural count beyond extraction's requirement count | 85% |\n74:## 3. Architecture\n79:Spec ──[V1-C: Structural audit]──> Extraction validated\n99:**Pipeline position**: The three post-merge checks run as a single non-LLM step between `merge` and `test-strategy` in the pipeline. The structural audit runs between `extract` and `generate` as an executor-level hook.\n105:## 4. Module 1: Obligation Scanner\n109:### Concept\n113:### Detection Axis\n117:### Implementation\n138:# --- Obligation vocabulary ---\n140:# Terms that CREATE an obligation (something deferred)\n155:# Terms that DISCHARGE an obligation (something fulfilled)\n168:# Compile patterns\n331:### Vocabulary Management\n350:### False Positive Mitigation\n355:- Scaffold terms inside code blocks (backtick-fenced) are treated as potential false positives and flagged at MEDIUM severity rather than failing the gate.\n361:## 5. Module 2: Integration Contract Extractor\n365:### Concept\n369:### Detection Axis\n373:### Implementation\n392:# --- Pattern definitions for integration contract detection ---\n393:# Expanded to cover all 7 categories from the integration mechanism taxonomy.\n447:# Patterns that indicate a roadmap task explicitly addresses wiring\n504:    \"\"\"Full audit result: all contracts and their coverage status.\"\"\"\n653:### Pattern Library Expansion\n671:## 6. Module 3: Fingerprint Extraction\n675:### Concept\n679:### Detection Axis\n683:### Implementation\n712:# Common non-specific constants to exclude from fingerprint extraction\n806:### Threshold Rationale\n813:- The 0.7 threshold means 30% of spec identifiers can be absent before the gate triggers, accommodating illustrative content.\n816:### Interaction with A-009 (\"Mentioned is not Planned\")\n822:## 7. Module 4: Spec Structural Audit\n824:<!-- Source: V1-C (spec structural audit) -->\n826:### Concept\n830:### Detection Axis\n834:### Implementation\n836:**File**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/spec_structural_audit.py` (new, ~80 LOC)\n839:\"\"\"Spec structural audit -- upstream guard on extraction quality.\n869:def audit_spec_structure(spec_text: str) -> SpecStructuralAudit:\n930:    Returns (passed, audit_result).\n939:    audit = audit_spec_structure(spec_text)\n941:    if audit.total_structural_indicators == 0:\n942:        return True, audit  # No indicators to compare against\n944:    ratio = extraction_total_requirements / audit.total_structural_indicators\n945:    return ratio >= threshold, audit\n948:### Enforcement Strategy\n950:<!-- Source: V1-C (spec structural audit), adapted per refactor-plan -->\n958:## 8. Gate Definition\n962:### New Gate: `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`\n964:**File**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` (modify existing)\n967:# --- Anti-Instinct Gate check functions ---\n972:    Runs V2-A obligation scanner on the anti-instinct audit report content.\n1017:# --- Gate definition ---\n1058:### Position in ALL_GATES\n1064:    (\"anti-instinct\", ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE),   # NEW\n1071:### Why a Separate Gate\n1075:The `MERGE_GATE` validates the merge step's output quality (heading hierarchy, cross-refs, duplicates). The anti-instinct checks validate cross-artifact semantic fidelity -- a different concern. Keeping them separate follows the existing pattern where each gate corresponds to one validation concern. The `MERGE_GATE` runs on the merged roadmap; the `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` runs on the anti-instinct audit report produced by the executor.\n1077:### Anti-Instinct Audit Report Format\n1079:The executor produces `output_dir / \"anti-instinct-audit.md\"` with frontmatter:\n1092:structural_audit_passed: true\n1096:This file is the gate artifact. The `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` validates its frontmatter fields. The executor writes it after running all three deterministic checks.\n1100:## 9. Executor Integration\n1104:### File: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py` (modify existing)\n1106:#### Change 1: Structural Audit After Extract\n1113:# In executor.py, after extract gate passes:\n1114:from .spec_structural_audit import check_extraction_adequacy\n1116:def _run_structural_audit(config, output_dir):\n1117:    \"\"\"Post-extract structural audit (V1-C upstream guard).\n1138:    passed, audit = check_extraction_adequacy(spec_text, total_requirements)\n1141:            \"Spec structural audit: extraction may be incomplete. \"\n1142:            f\"Spec has {audit.total_structural_indicators} structural indicators \"\n1144:            f\"(ratio: {total_requirements / max(audit.total_structural_indicators, 1):.2f}, \"\n1147:    return passed, audit\n1150:#### Change 2: Anti-Instinct Audit Step After Merge\n1154:This is a non-LLM step. The executor handles it specially (runs Python logic instead of a subprocess) when `step.id == \"anti-instinct\"`. The step appears in the pipeline step list for progress reporting and halt diagnostics.\n1157:# Add to _build_steps() between merge and test-strategy:\n1159:    id=\"anti-instinct\",\n1161:    output_file=out / \"anti-instinct-audit.md\",\n1162:    gate=ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE,\n1165:    retry_limit=0,  # Deterministic; retry would produce same result\n1169:#### Change 3: Anti-Instinct Audit Runner\n1176:def _run_anti_instinct_audit(config, output_dir):\n1177:    \"\"\"Run all three deterministic anti-instinct checks.\n1184:    Writes anti-instinct-audit.md with frontmatter for gate validation.\n1202:    # Write audit report\n1214:        f\"structural_audit_passed: true\",\n1267:    audit_path = output_dir / \"anti-instinct-audit.md\"\n1268:    audit_path.write_text(\"\\n\".join(report_lines), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n1273:#### Change 4: Import and Step ID Updates\n1276:# Add to executor.py imports:\n1277:from .gates import ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE\n1279:# Add \"anti-instinct\" to _get_all_step_ids() between \"merge\" and \"test-strategy\"\n1284:## 10. Prompt Modifications\n1288:### File: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/prompts.py` (modify existing)\n1290:#### Change 1: Integration Enumeration Block in `build_generate_prompt()`\n1297:## CRITICAL: Integration Point Enumeration\n1338:#### Change 2: Integration Wiring Dimension in `build_spec_fidelity_prompt()`\n1358:## 11. Contradiction Resolutions\n1377:## 12. File Change List\n1381:### New Files (4 source + 4 test)\n1388:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/spec_structural_audit.py` | V1-C | ~80 | Upstream extraction quality guard |\n1392:| `tests/roadmap/test_spec_structural_audit.py` | V1-C | ~60 | Structural indicator counting, ratio comparison |\n1394:### Modified Files (3)\n1398:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` | Add `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` definition with 3 semantic checks; add 3 check functions (`_no_undischarged_obligations`, `_integration_contracts_covered`, `_fingerprint_coverage_check`); update `ALL_GATES` list to insert `(\"anti-instinct\", ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE)` between `merge` and `test-strategy` | V2-A + V5-1 + V4-2 |\n1399:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py` | Add anti-instinct step to `_build_steps()`; add structural audit hook after extract (`_run_structural_audit`); add `_run_anti_instinct_audit()` function; add import for `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`; update `_get_all_step_ids()` to include `\"anti-instinct\"` | All |\n1402:### Total Impact\n1413:## 13. Implementation Phases\n1417:### Phase 1: Immediate (this specification)\n1419:All content in Sections 4-10 above. Four new modules, one new gate, executor wiring, prompt modifications. Zero LLM calls added. Estimated implementation: 4-6 sprint tasks.\n1425:integration_contracts.py --+--> gates.py --> executor.py\n1427:spec_structural_audit.py --------------------->+\n1434:4. `spec_structural_audit.py` + tests\n1435:5. `gates.py` -- add `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` with all 3 semantic checks\n1436:6. `executor.py` -- wire anti-instinct step + structural audit hook\n1440:### Phase 2: Deferred Items\n1454:## 14. Shared Assumptions and Known Risks\n1463:| A-007 | SemanticCheck single-file limitation | Multi-file checks need workarounds | Executor-level workaround (write audit report, validate frontmatter). Phase 2: model extension |\n1470:## 15. V5-3 AP-001 Subsumption by V2-A\n1481:If additional anti-pattern rules are needed in Phase 2, the rule engine can be introduced at that time with V2-A as a delegate for AP-001.\n1485:## 16. Rejected Alternatives"}]},"uuid":"86b77705-4e9b-4168-91c5-34a1a7534a64","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:37.485Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"603b3ab8-5b44-44c0-983e-6479ef011924","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
