{"parentUuid":"613f0951-8f03-448e-b32b-4453b10f9cad","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"c899109a-85f0-4ce2-8d4b-537fc48bb9f2","agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ly88P8JxIoTbc6yYUyUyZhCe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Unified Audit Gating System v1.2.1 — Release Specification (Implementation-Ready)\n     2→\n     3→Document status: **Draft for sign-off**\n     4→Decision baseline date: **2026-03-03**\n     5→Primary intent: direct input for roadmap generation and phased tasklist creation.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 0. Evidence Model and Decision Method\n    10→\n    11→### 0.1 Deterministic findings (normative in this spec)\n    12→Deterministic items are requirements, invariants, contracts, and state/decision rules that are directly specified in source artifacts and are testable/replayable.\n    13→\n    14→### 0.2 Heuristic judgments (advisory in this spec)\n    15→Heuristic items are operational recommendations (e.g., rollout pacing, UX friction mitigation) derived from reviews/risk analysis and are non-authoritative unless promoted to a locked decision.\n    16→\n    17→### 0.3 Citation rule used\n    18→Critical claims cite source file + section label. If section labels are absent, file heading context is used.\n    19→\n    20→---\n    21→\n    22→## 1. Release Scope and Goals\n    23→\n    24→### 1.1 Scope\n    25→Implement a unified audit-gating capability that blocks completion/release transitions unless the corresponding gate passes at three scopes:\n    26→1. Task gate\n    27→2. Milestone gate\n    28→3. Release gate\n    29→\n    30→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Goal; Task-Level Gate; Milestone-Level Gate; Release-Level Gate)\n    31→\n    32→### 1.2 Primary goals\n    33→1. Deterministic pass/fail gating with evidence-backed outputs\n    34→2. Explicit audit workflow states for all scopes\n    35→3. Single primary user interface (`/sc:audit-gate`)\n    36→4. Rollout-safe enforcement (shadow → soft → full)\n    37→\n    38→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Locked Decisions, Non-Functional Requirements, Command & Enforcement; `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Command/API Surface, Migration/Rollout; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → v1.1 Delta Summary)\n    39→\n    40→### 1.3 Out-of-scope for v1.2.1\n    41→- New non-gating product features unrelated to transition control\n    42→- Security hardening expansions not required for correctness of gate transitions\n    43→- Full auto-tuning of profiles during rollout (deferred)\n    44→\n    45→(Constraint source: user hard requirement + `executive-summary.md` → deferred improvements)\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## 2. Locked Decisions, Non-Goals, and Contradiction Resolution\n    50→\n    51→### 2.1 Locked decisions (authoritative)\n    52→1. Configurable strictness/profile behavior exists\n    53→2. Tier-1 gate is required even for LIGHT/EXEMPT flows\n    54→3. Overrides allowed only for task/milestone (never release)\n    55→4. Single primary command interface\n    56→5. Explicit `audit_*` states are required\n    57→\n    58→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Locked Decisions; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → Locked User Decisions)\n    59→\n    60→### 2.2 Non-goals\n    61→- Release-level override capability\n    62→- LLM/agent heuristics as source of truth for pass/fail\n    63→\n    64→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Locked Decisions/Acceptance Criteria; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → v1.1 Delta Summary A)\n    65→\n    66→### 2.3 Contradictions and winning decisions\n    67→\n    68→| Contradiction | Evidence | Winner in v1.2.1 | Rationale |\n    69→|---|---|---|---|\n    70→| `--strictness standard|strict` vs profile set `strict|standard|legacy_migration` | `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Flags; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → v1.1 Delta Summary B | Canonical model is `--profile strict|standard|legacy_migration`; `--strictness` retained only as temporary alias in shadow/soft, removed at full | Needed for deterministic policy selection and migration compatibility (`design-delta-v1.2.md` → Change 1) |\n    71→| Shorthand state expression can imply terminal transition from failed branch | `02-design-spec-v1.md` → State Machine; `state-machine-validation.md` → Current gap | Explicit legal/illegal transition table is authoritative | Removes ambiguity and enables validator enforcement |\n    72→| “State machine hardening added” vs retry/backoff still open | `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → Delta D + Open Items (3) | v1.2.1 must lock concrete retry/backoff/timeout semantics before GO | Required for deadlock resistance and reproducibility |\n    73→| Rollout phases present but rollback/safe-disable not concrete | `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Migration/Rollout; `05-review-checklist.md` → Section 8 | v1.2.1 defines explicit rollback triggers/contracts | Checklist compliance and operational safety |\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→## 3. Canonical Terminology and Policy Model\n    78→\n    79→### 3.1 Canonical terms\n    80→- **Scope**: `task | milestone | release`\n    81→- **Tier**: `Tier-1(task), Tier-2(milestone), Tier-3(release)`\n    82→- **Profile**: `strict | standard | legacy_migration`\n    83→- **Gate status**: `passed | failed`\n    84→- **Failure class**: `policy | transient | system | timeout | unknown`\n    85→\n    86→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → tier goals; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → profile + schema direction; `design-delta-v1.2.md` → failure-class taxonomy)\n    87→\n    88→### 3.2 Strictness vs profile resolution (normative)\n    89→1. Runtime policy resolver consumes `profile` as canonical input.\n    90→2. If `strictness` is provided, map `strictness=strict|standard` to `profile=strict|standard`.\n    91→3. `legacy_migration` cannot be expressed through `strictness`; must use `profile`.\n    92→4. At full enforcement, `strictness` alias is rejected.\n    93→\n    94→(Source: `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Change 1)\n    95→\n    96→---\n    97→\n    98→## 4. Normative State Machine\n    99→\n   100→### 4.1 Legal transitions\n   101→\n   102→#### Task scope\n   103→- `in_progress -> ready_for_audit_task`\n   104→- `ready_for_audit_task -> audit_task_running`\n   105→- `audit_task_running -> audit_task_passed | audit_task_failed`\n   106→- `audit_task_passed -> completed`\n   107→- `audit_task_failed -> ready_for_audit_task` (retry path)\n   108→- `audit_task_failed -> completed` only with approved task override\n   109→\n   110→#### Milestone scope\n   111→- `in_progress -> ready_for_audit_milestone`\n   112→- `ready_for_audit_milestone -> audit_milestone_running`\n   113→- `audit_milestone_running -> audit_milestone_passed | audit_milestone_failed`\n   114→- `audit_milestone_passed -> completed`\n   115→- `audit_milestone_failed -> ready_for_audit_milestone` (retry path)\n   116→- `audit_milestone_failed -> completed` only with approved milestone override\n   117→\n   118→#### Release scope\n   119→- `in_progress -> ready_for_audit_release`\n   120→- `ready_for_audit_release -> audit_release_running`\n   121→- `audit_release_running -> audit_release_passed | audit_release_failed`\n   122→- `audit_release_passed -> released`\n   123→- `audit_release_failed -> ready_for_audit_release` (retry path)\n   124→- `audit_release_failed -> released` is forbidden\n   125→\n   126→(Source: `state-machine-validation.md` → proposed normative form; `01-requirements-spec.md` → Acceptance Criteria; `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Failure/Override Policy)\n   127→\n   128→### 4.2 Illegal transitions (minimum mandatory set)\n   129→1. `in_progress -> completed/released` (bypass)\n   130→2. `ready_for_audit_* -> completed/released`\n   131→3. `audit_*_running -> completed/released`\n   132→4. `audit_*_failed -> completed` without approved override (task/milestone only)\n   133→5. `audit_release_failed -> released` always\n   134→6. Any transition from terminal state except explicit reopen operation\n   135→\n   136→(Source: `state-machine-validation.md` → Illegal transitions)\n   137→\n   138→### 4.3 Override rules (normative)\n   139→- Task and milestone may override failed gate only with approved `OverrideRecord`\n   140→- Release override is forbidden by invariant\n   141→\n   142→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Locked Decisions/Acceptance Criteria; `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Failure/Override Policy)\n   143→\n   144→### 4.4 Timeout, retry, recovery semantics\n   145→1. `audit_*_running` uses lease + heartbeat.\n   146→2. Missing heartbeat past timeout causes `audit_*_failed(timeout)`.\n   147→3. Retry is bounded by per-scope attempt budget.\n   148→4. Retry exhaustion remains failed and blocks completion/release.\n   149→5. Requeue allowed only while budget remains.\n   150→\n   151→(Source: `state-machine-validation.md` → Stuck-state handling/recovery; `risk-register-v1.2.md` → R2; `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Add 4)\n   152→\n   153→---\n   154→\n   155→## 5. Deterministic Gate Decision Contract\n   156→\n   157→### 5.1 Failure classes\n   158→- `policy`: rule/threshold violation\n   159→- `transient`: recoverable execution issue\n   160→- `system`: non-recoverable runner/system error\n   161→- `timeout`: stale/expired running state\n   162→- `unknown`: unmapped condition (fail-safe)\n   163→\n   164→(Source: `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Add 2; `01-requirements-spec.md` → fail-safe defaults)\n   165→\n   166→### 5.2 Pass/fail rules (normative)\n   167→1. Any blocking check failure => gate `failed`.\n   168→2. Unknown/missing deterministic inputs => `failed`.\n   169→3. Missing evidence for failed check => `failed` and non-completable.\n   170→4. Completion/release transitions require latest gate `passed` except approved task/milestone override path.\n   171→\n   172→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Non-Functional Requirements/Acceptance Criteria; `metrics-and-gates.md` → M5; `state-machine-validation.md`)\n   173→\n   174→### 5.3 Evidence requirements\n   175→Every failed check must include at least one evidence reference:\n   176→- file path OR\n   177→- `file:line`\n   178→\n   179→Drift summary must separate `edited` vs `non-edited`.\n   180→\n   181→(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Reporting + Non-Functional Requirements; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → GateResult schema)\n   182→\n   183→---\n   184→\n   185→## 6. Data Contracts and Versioning\n   186→\n   187→### 6.1 GateResult (normative v1.2.1)\n   188→Required fields:\n   189→- `version`\n   190→- `gate_run_id`\n   191→- `scope`, `entity_id`, `profile`\n   192→- `status`, `score`, `threshold`\n   193→- `checks[]` (includes severity + evidence)\n   194→- `drift_summary` (`edited`, `non_edited`)\n   195→- `override` block\n   196→- `timing` block\n   197→- `artifacts` block\n   198→- `failure_class` (v1.2 addition)\n   199→\n   200→(Source: `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → Canonical GateResult; `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Add 2)\n   201→\n   202→### 6.2 OverrideRecord (normative v1.2.1)\n   203→Required fields:\n   204→- `record_id`, `scope`, `entity_id`\n   205→- `actor`\n   206→- `reason_code`, `reason_text`\n   207→- `created_at`, `expires_at`\n   208→- `linked_gate_run_id`\n   209→- `approver`, `approval_state`, `review_due_at` (v1.2 governance addition)\n   210→\n   211→(Source: `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → Canonical OverrideRecord; `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Change 2)\n   212→\n   213→### 6.3 Transition event schema (normative)\n   214→`GateTransitionEvent` minimum fields:\n   215→- `event_id`, `correlation_id`, `occurred_at`\n   216→- `scope`, `entity_id`\n   217→- `from_state`, `to_state`\n   218→- `cause` (`check_failure|timeout|retry|override|manual_reopen|system_error`)\n   219→- `gate_run_id` (nullable when pre-run)\n   220→\n   221→`GateCheckEvent` minimum fields:\n   222→- `event_id`, `correlation_id`, `gate_run_id`\n   223→- `check_id`, `severity`, `outcome`, `evidence_refs[]`\n   224→\n   225→(Source: `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Add 6; `state-machine-validation.md` → correlation ID replay requirement)\n   226→\n   227→### 6.4 Versioning policy\n   228→- Backward-compatible additions: minor bump\n   229→- Breaking field/semantic changes: major bump\n   230→- Gate evaluator must reject unsupported major versions as `failed(unknown)`\n   231→\n   232→(Source basis: determinism/fail-safe requirements in `01-requirements-spec.md`)\n   233→\n   234→---\n   235→\n   236→## 7. Rollout Contract\n   237→\n   238→### 7.1 Phases\n   239→1. **Shadow**: collect decisions/metrics; no hard business blocking\n   240→2. **Soft**: selective enforcement by profile/scope\n   241→3. **Full**: global enforcement\n   242→\n   243→(Source: `02-design-spec-v1.md` → Migration/Rollout; `04-design-v1.1-delta-handoff.md` → Delta G)\n   244→\n   245→### 7.2 Promotion criteria\n   246→- Shadow -> Soft: pass M1, M4, M5, M7, M9\n   247→- Soft -> Full: pass M1–M12 for two consecutive windows + pass rollback drill (M10)\n   248→\n   249→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md` → Gate thresholds by rollout phase)\n   250→\n   251→### 7.3 Rollback / safe-disable triggers (normative)\n   252→Immediate rollback to prior phase if any occurs:\n   253→1. M4 determinism breach below threshold\n   254→2. Any M5 evidence completeness failure\n   255→3. Unresolved stale-running incident (M7 fail)\n   256→4. Failed rollback drill in current window (M10 fail)\n   257→5. Transition validator bypass discovered\n   258→\n   259→Rollback order: `full -> soft -> shadow`. Emergency safe-disable keeps shadow artifact production enabled.\n   260→\n   261→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md`; `risk-register-v1.2.md` R1/R2/R8/R10; `design-delta-v1.2.md` Add 5)\n   262→\n   263→---\n   264→\n   265→## 8. KPI/SLO Framework\n   266→\n   267→### 8.1 Provisional vs normative thresholds\n   268→- Thresholds in current KPI table are **provisional** in shadow mode.\n   269→- They become **normative** only after calibration and explicit approval at phase gate.\n   270→\n   271→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md` → KPI/SLO table note)\n   272→\n   273→### 8.2 Calibration method (normative)\n   274→1. Collect M1–M12 for at least two shadow windows.\n   275→2. Compute baseline distributions and replay stability.\n   276→3. Propose thresholds and warning/fail bands.\n   277→4. Obtain owner sign-off for normative activation at soft/full gate.\n   278→\n   279→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md` → Shadow and phase gates)\n   280→\n   281→### 8.3 Warning/fail bands (authoritative examples)\n   282→- Runtime bands M1–M3 as defined in KPI table\n   283→- Determinism floor M4 strict by tier\n   284→- Evidence completeness M5 has no warning band (any miss is fail)\n   285→\n   286→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md`)\n   287→\n   288→### 8.4 Heuristic operational guidance\n   289→If runtime degrades but determinism/evidence remain compliant, optimize check execution before relaxing policy thresholds.\n   290→\n   291→(Source: `metrics-and-gates.md` → Heuristic judgments)\n   292→\n   293→---\n   294→\n   295→## 9. Governance\n   296→\n   297→### 9.1 Override approval model (normative)\n   298→- Scope eligibility: task/milestone only\n   299→- Required approval metadata: approver identity, approval state, review due date\n   300→- Incomplete override metadata is invalid and blocks completion\n   301→\n   302→(Source: `05-review-checklist.md` → Section 6; `design-delta-v1.2.md` → Change 2; `metrics-and-gates.md` → M9)\n   303→\n   304→### 9.2 Owner responsibilities\n   305→- **Policy owner**: profile thresholds + severity mapping\n   306→- **State-machine owner**: legal/illegal transition validator correctness\n   307→- **Reliability owner**: timeout/retry/backoff + stale recovery\n   308→- **Migration owner**: rollout/rollback readiness and drills\n   309→- **Program manager**: open-decision closure with owner+deadline tracking\n   310→\n   311→(Source: `risk-register-v1.2.md` owners; `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` blockers)\n   312→\n   313→### 9.3 Decision deadlines (normative requirement)\n   314→All open blocking decisions must have:\n   315→- Owner\n   316→- UTC decision deadline\n   317→- Effective rollout phase\n   318→\n   319→No GO decision without all three assigned.\n   320→\n   321→(Source: `05-review-checklist.md` → Section 10; `executive-summary.md` → critical decisions; `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`)\n   322→\n   323→---\n   324→\n   325→## 10. Implementation Mapping\n   326→\n   327→### 10.1 Phase plan\n   328→- **Phase 0**: design/policy lock and owner/date assignments\n   329→- **Phase 1**: deterministic contracts + evaluator + transition validator\n   330→- **Phase 2**: runtime controls (lease/heartbeat/retry/recovery)\n   331→- **Phase 3**: sprint CLI integration + override governance flow + report persistence\n   332→- **Phase 4**: rollout execution + KPI gates + rollback drills\n   333→\n   334→(Source: `implementation-plan-v1.2.md`)\n   335→\n   336→### 10.2 File-level change map (implementation target)\n   337→1. `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/models.py` — states/enums/constraints/profile fields\n   338→2. `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/tui.py` — completion/release guards and operator guidance\n   339→3. `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate/SKILL.md` — command behavior/profile/output contract\n   340→4. `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate-protocol/SKILL.md` — deterministic evaluator and transition legality/recovery flow\n   341→5. `src/superclaude/agents/*.md` — enrichment-only role clarification\n   342→6. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_state_machine.py` — legal/illegal transitions + stuck-state recovery\n   343→7. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_profiles.py` — profile determinism + severity behavior\n   344→8. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_overrides.py` — scope-limited override governance\n   345→9. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_rollout.py` — shadow/soft/full + rollback behavior\n   346→\n   347→(Source: `implementation-plan-v1.2.md` → File-level change map)\n   348→\n   349→### 10.3 Acceptance criteria per phase\n   350→- Phase 0: all blocking decisions closed with owner/date\n   351→- Phase 1: deterministic replay stability for same input; fail-safe unknown handling\n   352→- Phase 2: timeout/retry paths terminate deterministically (no deadlocks)\n   353→- Phase 3: transition blocking/override rules enforced per scope\n   354→- Phase 4: phase gates pass by KPI criteria and rollback drill success\n   355→\n   356→(Source: `implementation-plan-v1.2.md`; `metrics-and-gates.md`)\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→## 11. Checklist Closure Matrix (Sections 1–10)\n   361→\n   362→Source checklist: `05-review-checklist.md`.\n   363→\n   364→| Checklist section | Current status | Closure condition for GO | Evidence source |\n   365→|---|---|---|---|\n   366→| 1. Context completeness | PASS (conditional) | Assign owners/deadlines to open items | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   367→| 2. Command/API surface | PASS (conditional) | Approve canonical `--profile` and alias policy | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `design-delta-v1.2.md` |\n   368→| 3. State machine/invariants | PASS (conditional) | Enforce legal/illegal transitions in implementation | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `state-machine-validation.md` |\n   369→| 4. Data contracts | PASS (conditional) | Finalize event contracts + compatibility rules | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   370→| 5. Tier model soundness | PASS (conditional) | Finalize numeric thresholds + major severity behavior | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   371→| 6. Override/governance | PASS (conditional) | Finalize approver model + review cadence | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   372→| 7. Sprint CLI integration | PASS (conditional) | Integrate deterministic transition validator before completion transitions | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   373→| 8. Migration/backward compatibility | PASS (conditional) | Approve rollback/safe-disable trigger contract | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   374→| 9. Risk/reliability controls | PASS (conditional) | Finalize retry/backoff/timeout values and budgets | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `risk-register-v1.2.md` |\n   375→| 10. Implementation readiness | NO-GO (current) | Close all 4 blockers with owner/date and reflect in artifacts | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `executive-summary.md` |\n   376→\n   377→---\n   378→\n   379→## 12. Final Release Decision Gate\n   380→\n   381→### 12.1 GO criteria\n   382→All must be true:\n   383→1. Blocking decisions closed (profile thresholds, major severity behavior, retry/backoff/timeout, rollback triggers)\n   384→2. Transition legality and recovery semantics implemented and tested\n   385→3. Deterministic contract and evidence completeness validated\n   386→4. Checklist sections 2,3,4,6,7 fully pass; remaining sections pass or have non-critical tracked gaps\n   387→5. Owners/deadlines assigned for any residual non-blocking items\n   388→\n   389→(Source: `05-review-checklist.md` → Minimum Acceptance Threshold + Section 10; `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`)\n   390→\n   391→### 12.2 NO-GO criteria\n   392→Any one is sufficient:\n   393→- Any unresolved blocker from section 11\n   394→- Missing owner/deadline on blocking decision\n   395→- Determinism/evidence gate failure (M4/M5)\n   396→- Release override path exists or can be triggered\n   397→\n   398→(Source: `executive-summary.md`; `metrics-and-gates.md`; `01-requirements-spec.md`)\n   399→\n   400→### 12.3 Current blocker list\n   401→1. Profile thresholds and task-tier major-severity behavior not finalized\n   402→2. Retry/backoff/timeout values not finalized\n   403→3. Rollback/safe-disable triggers not finalized\n   404→4. Open blocking decisions not yet assigned owner+deadline in final artifact set\n   405→\n   406→(Source: `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` → Blocking items)\n   407→\n   408→### 12.4 Required user decisions\n   409→1. Approve canonical profile model and numeric thresholds\n   410→2. Approve major-severity behavior at task tier under `standard`\n   411→3. Approve retry/backoff/timeout values and max attempts\n   412→4. Approve rollback/safe-disable objective triggers\n   413→5. Approve override governance model (single vs dual approver) and review cadence\n   414→\n   415→(Source: `executive-summary.md` → Critical decisions)\n   416→\n   417→---\n   418→\n   419→## Top 5 Immediate Actions\n   420→1. Finalize and sign off profile thresholds + major-severity behavior.\n   421→2. Finalize retry/backoff/timeout and stale-state budgets.\n   422→3. Ratify explicit legal/illegal transition table as implementation authority.\n   423→4. Approve rollback/safe-disable triggers and phase regression policy.\n   424→5. Assign owner + UTC deadline + effective phase to each blocking decision.\n   425→\n   426→## Top 5 Deferred Improvements\n   427→1. Add readiness preview mode pre-gate.\n   428→2. Improve human-readable remediation hints in gate failures.\n   429→3. Add trend dashboards for drift/override quality.\n   430→4. Add profile auto-tuning recommendations from shadow telemetry.\n   431→5. Optimize long-horizon artifact retention policy.\n   432→\n   433→## Open Decisions Needed from User\n   434→| Decision | Owner | Deadline (UTC) | Effective phase |\n   435→|---|---|---|---|\n   436→| Profile thresholds + major-severity behavior | [TBD] | [TBD] | Soft |\n   437→| Retry/backoff/timeout policy | [TBD] | [TBD] | Soft |\n   438→| Rollback/safe-disable triggers | [TBD] | [TBD] | Full |\n   439→| Override approver model + review cadence | [TBD] | [TBD] | Soft |\n   440→| `--strictness` alias deprecation date | [TBD] | [TBD] | Full |\n   441→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"7238159a-ddc4-45ab-b49e-bcc98