nistic replay stability for same input; fail-safe unknown handling\n   352→- Phase 2: timeout/retry paths terminate deterministically (no deadlocks)\n   353→- Phase 3: transition blocking/override rules enforced per scope\n   354→- Phase 4: phase gates pass by KPI criteria and rollback drill success\n   355→\n   356→(Source: `implementation-plan-v1.2.md`; `metrics-and-gates.md`)\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→## 11. Checklist Closure Matrix (Sections 1–10)\n   361→\n   362→Source checklist: `05-review-checklist.md`.\n   363→\n   364→| Checklist section | Current status | Closure condition for GO | Evidence source |\n   365→|---|---|---|---|\n   366→| 1. Context completeness | PASS (conditional) | Assign owners/deadlines to open items | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   367→| 2. Command/API surface | PASS (conditional) | Approve canonical `--profile` and alias policy | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `design-delta-v1.2.md` |\n   368→| 3. State machine/invariants | PASS (conditional) | Enforce legal/illegal transitions in implementation | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `state-machine-validation.md` |\n   369→| 4. Data contracts | PASS (conditional) | Finalize event contracts + compatibility rules | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   370→| 5. Tier model soundness | PASS (conditional) | Finalize numeric thresholds + major severity behavior | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   371→| 6. Override/governance | PASS (conditional) | Finalize approver model + review cadence | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   372→| 7. Sprint CLI integration | PASS (conditional) | Integrate deterministic transition validator before completion transitions | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   373→| 8. Migration/backward compatibility | PASS (conditional) | Approve rollback/safe-disable trigger contract | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n   374→| 9. Risk/reliability controls | PASS (conditional) | Finalize retry/backoff/timeout values and budgets | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `risk-register-v1.2.md` |\n   375→| 10. Implementation readiness | NO-GO (current) | Close all 4 blockers with owner/date and reflect in artifacts | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`, `executive-summary.md` |\n   376→\n   377→---\n   378→\n   379→## 12. Final Release Decision Gate\n   380→\n   381→### 12.1 GO criteria\n   382→All must be true:\n   383→1. Blocking decisions closed (profile thresholds, major severity behavior, retry/backoff/timeout, rollback triggers)\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"b57dad76-ed8e-4916-962d-643480318279","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:49:27.828Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0d8915ac-b722-403a-b382-165ad57b71d0","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
