{"parentUuid":"43172913-56c1-4dc7-b377-49970aa09329","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","message":{"id":"resp_0ca2d74fb95959470169b9a2385d3081989a3e2c3ea71754c6","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":54930,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":338,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_vNArPs6IrGli1ODIQ2WWAIJO","name":"mcp__sequential-thinking__sequentialthinking","input":{"thought":"Classifications: SE-001 overlapping with v3.0 and v3.1. v3.0 adds post-task gate hook and uses gate_passed() in sprint/executor; v3.1 mandates unknown/missing deterministic inputs => failed and transition validator before completion transitions. Not fully redundant because SE-001 also asks to log reasons on successful gate calls and check empty output in gate_passed(); v3.1 doesn't spell that out. SE-002 overlapping with v3.1 because both address restart/resume semantics but v3.1 uses explicit audit states/transition events, not task_uid. Needs revise to align UID with state machine / gate_run_id rather than ad hoc non-DONE resume. SE-003 unaffected: execution-mode prompt selection is orthogonal; no direct replacement in refs. SE-004 overlapping with v3.1 because retry bounded budgets and exhaustion semantics cover repeated failures; auto-diagnostic after N failures could complement but must hook only on exhaustion or via state machine transitions. SE-005 contradicted by v3.1 because failure taxonomy is canonical (`policy|transient|system|timeout|unknown`) and GateResult/checks already include severity; a separate SEV1/2/3 enum on same gate failure events conflicts with canonical failure_class and unresolved major-severity behavior. v3.0 says zero changes to existing gate infrastructure, so SE-005 not affected by v3.0; v3.05 unaffected.","thoughtNumber":3,"totalThoughts":4,"nextThoughtNeeded":true}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"b8eff5f1-411a-4e7c-ac88-93cb6c751cdc","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:49:36.389Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
