{"parentUuid":"bdd6212d-1226-4602-85d0-f41ccb99ba10","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a7e5e78a0f8cf79ca","message":{"id":"resp_0821ee3fcb078d210169b9a252febc819bbdb48940f2199ee7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55627,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":1954,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compared `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-sprint-executor.md` against:\n- `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`\n- `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`\n- `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`\n\nFindings:\n\n**ITEM SE-001** — Fail-Closed Gate Completion Logic  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item requires fail-closed completion in `sprint/executor.py` and stricter `gate_passed()` semantics, including empty-output failure and completion only on affirmative evidence (`improve-sprint-executor.md`, lines 25-33).  \n  - v3.0 already inserts a new post-task gate hook into `sprint/executor.py` “after `_classify_from_result_file()` returns, before the task status is finalized” and calls `gate_passed()` in full mode (`wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, Section 4.5, lines 537-566; file manifest lines 598-600).  \n  - v3.1 makes unknown/missing deterministic inputs fail-safe and requires latest gate `passed` before completion/release (`unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`, Section 5.2, lines 166-171), plus requires integrating a deterministic transition validator before completion transitions (Section 11 matrix, lines 372-374).  \n  - v3.05 is roadmap-only; its modified files are under `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/` and not sprint execution (`anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`, lines 1398-1400).  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep only the parts not clearly subsumed: explicit “empty output file” handling in `gate_passed()` and trace logging of `(passed, reason)` even on success. Reframe the completion logic to align with v3.1’s transition validator rather than adding independent completion heuristics.\n\n**ITEM SE-002** — Per-Item UID Tracking for Sub-Phase Restartability  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item adds `task_uid` and resume-from-first-non-DONE behavior in `sprint/executor.py` / TurnLedger (`improve-sprint-executor.md`, lines 46-55).  \n  - v3.1 introduces explicit audit task states: `ready_for_audit_task`, `audit_task_running`, `audit_task_passed`, `audit_task_failed`, with retry path `audit_task_failed -> ready_for_audit_task` (Section 4.1, lines 102-108).  \n  - v3.1 also defines transition events and correlation fields (`GateTransitionEvent`, `gate_run_id`, causes including `retry`) that become the canonical replay/resume structure (Section 6.3, lines 213-225).  \n  - Phase mapping in v3.1 puts retry/recovery semantics and sprint CLI integration inside the same state-machine model (Section 10.1, lines 327-333).  \n  - v3.05 again does not touch sprint models/executor.  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — do not keep the current “status != DONE” resume rule as-is. If retained, `task_uid` should become an implementation detail tied to v3.1’s canonical audit states and transition/gate-run identity, so resume logic is state-machine-aware rather than a parallel ad hoc status tracker.\n\n**ITEM SE-003** — Three-Mode Execution for Mid-Phase Resume  \n- Status: UNAFFECTED  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item adds `ExecutionMode` (`NORMAL`, `INCOMPLETE_RESUME`, `CORRECTION`) and prompt construction differences in `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/process.py`, with mode selection recorded by sprint executor (`improve-sprint-executor.md`, lines 67-75).  \n  - v3.1 defines legal states, retry semantics, and transition blocking, but does not specify prompt-mode branching or executor prompt-context modes for resumed work (`unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`, Sections 4.1, 4.4, 10.2).  \n  - v3.0 only adds a wiring gate post-task hook and explicitly says “Zero changes to existing gate infrastructure” beyond the new consumer path (`wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, lines 913-914).  \n  - v3.05 modifies only roadmap executor/gates/prompts (`anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`, lines 1398-1400).  \n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS — this remains independent of the three refactors, though later implementation should map the mode decision onto v3.1 state names for consistency.\n\n**ITEM SE-004** — Auto-Trigger Diagnostic on N Consecutive Gate Failures  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item adds a consecutive-failure counter and triggers `run_diagnostic_chain()` after threshold N (`improve-sprint-executor.md`, lines 87-96).  \n  - v3.1 already makes retry/recovery semantics canonical: `audit_*_running` uses lease/heartbeat, retry is bounded by per-scope attempt budget, and retry exhaustion remains failed and blocks completion/release (Section 4.4, lines 144-151).  \n  - v3.1’s implementation map explicitly reserves Phase 2 for runtime controls including retry/recovery and Phase 3 for sprint CLI integration (Section 10.1, lines 327-333).  \n  - Because the retry budget is supposed to be authoritative, an independent “N consecutive failures” trigger partially duplicates the retry-exhaustion policy.  \n  - v3.05 is unrelated except for roadmap-level halt diagnostics, not sprint retry policy (`anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`, line 1154).  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep only as a subordinate hook to v3.1 retry semantics, e.g. trigger diagnostics on retry exhaustion or on specific failure classes, not on an independent executor-local counter that could diverge from the canonical attempt budget.\n\n**ITEM SE-005** — Three-Tier Severity for Gate Failure Reports  \n- Status: CONTRADICTED  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item proposes a new `GateFailureSeverity` enum in `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` with `SEV1_BLOCK | SEV2_CYCLE | SEV3_ADVISORY`, and wants `gate_passed()` / sprint executor to classify gate failures using that taxonomy (`improve-sprint-executor.md`, lines 108-116).  \n  - v3.1 establishes a canonical failure taxonomy: `policy | transient | system | timeout | unknown` (Section 3.1, lines 79-86; Section 5.1, lines 157-164), and adds `failure_class` to the normative `GateResult` schema (Section 6.1, lines 187-199).  \n  - v3.1 also says profile thresholds and severity behavior are still a blocking decision to be finalized, not something a side enum should hardcode (`unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`, lines 370-383, 400-413).  \n  - v3.1 assigns “profile thresholds + severity mapping” to policy ownership, indicating there is already a canonical severity/policy layer under audit gating governance (line 305).  \n  - v3.0 explicitly preserves existing gate infrastructure and does not define a competing severity taxonomy (`wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, lines 683-686, 913-914).  \n  - v3.05 makes no model changes to shared pipeline contracts and states “Existing model changes: 0” (`/config/.claude/projects/-config-workspace-IronClaude/caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5/tool-results/call_gccA6vjLwmFfe3qM2P5Lyus5.txt`, line 1409).  \n- Recommendation: REMOVE — this item creates a parallel classification system for the same gate-failure events and conflicts with v3.1’s canonical `failure_class` contract and unresolved governed severity behavior.\n\nOverall disposition: `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-sprint-executor.md` is heavily impacted by the refactors, especially v3.1. SE-001, SE-002, and SE-004 should survive only as narrowed revisions aligned to the unified audit-gating state machine and transition validator; SE-003 remains independently valid; SE-005 should be removed because it conflicts with v3.1’s canonical failure taxonomy and governed severity model."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"857d8fbb-0aa2-4dcb-967d-19856c236098","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:50:33.707Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
